    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Yeap, I've just noticed it's captured on the default error handler, which I override. I dont feel comfortable with the error handler being called on non-(server)error scenarios, and I think noone is handling this kind of errors. In fact, the examples on the [official error handling guide](http://expressjs.com/es/guide/error-handling.html) doesn't handle those either. Maybe it should be treated just like any other protocol error, and never reach the app code.\n",
